What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Network-as-a-Service (Naas) Market?

Market Analysis and Size

In the Network-as-a-Service (NaaS) market, businesses leverage cloud-based solutions to scale their networks dynamically, driving efficiency and flexibility. This advancement offers cost-effective subscription models, enabling companies to tailor network resources to their needs. The benefits include reduced infrastructure costs, simplified management, and rapid deployment of services, fostering innovation and competitiveness.

The global network-as-a-service (Naas) market size was valued at USD 11.56 billion in 2023, is projected to reach USD 104.66 billion by 2031, with a CAGR of 31.70% during the forecast period 2024 to 2031. In addition to the market insights such as market value, growth rate, market segments, geographical coverage, market players, and market scenario, the market report curated by the Data Bridge Market Research team includes in-depth expert analysis, import/export analysis, pricing analysis, production consumption analysis, and pestle analysis.

